name: Publisher
definition: role of person(s) or organization(s) responsible for the printing or distribution of an item, whether in digital or print (physical) form
label: publisher
explanatoryNote: Publishers may also include banks, government agencies and the like.

name: Publication
label: publication
definition: document offered for general distribution and usually produced in multiple copies
explanatoryNote: A publication can be anything made public by print (such as a newspaper, magazine, pamphlet, letter, telegram, via computer modem or program, or in a poster, brochure or pamphlet), orally, or by broadcast (radio, television).

name: MarketDataProvider
definition: publisher of data relevant to financial markets
label: market data provider
explanatoryNote: Market data providers include exchanges and independent data vendors, among others. Market valuation and related control and risk processes typically require explicit documentation of the source for a given market rate, such as an interest rate benchmark, exchange rate, stock prices, and so forth.

name: isPublishedBy
definition: identifies the independent party (i.e., the individual or organization) that disseminates the material
label: is published by

name: hasPublisher
label: has publisher
definition: indicates the party in the role of issuing the information

name: publishes
definition: prepares and issues material for public consumption
label: publishes
